2025-09-26 16:06:05,360 - INFO - Strategy Summary: After analyzing the provided pipetting data, here is the analysis:

1. BEST PERFORMING EXPERIMENTS:
The best performance was observed in the fourth experiment (trial_index 3) with the lowest deviation of 9.714468 and a variability of 4.029496. This was achieved with the following parameters: aspirate_speed 16 uL/s, dispense_speed 30 uL/s, aspirate_wait_time 4.259607 seconds, dispense_wait_time 27.094172 seconds, retract_speed 14.326069 uL/s, pre_asp_air_vol 0.058002 mL, post_asp_air_vol 0.084892 mL, overaspirate_vol 0.013357 mL.

2. OBSERVED PATTERNS:
Lower aspirate_speed and higher dispense_speed seem to correlate with lower deviation. Longer dispense_wait_time can also contribute to lower deviation and variability. 

Based on the above observations, the following recommendations are proposed:

Recommendation 1:
